From a94862f8a2d952d69c4d0d7c67dafde77aaf423e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 05:37:10 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix(agents): classify exhaustion cause distinctly (credit vs
 subscription)

A terminal limit ResultMessage conflated three distinct exhaustion causes
into one generic subscription-quota report regardless of the matched
signal, so a metered ANTHROPIC_API_KEY out of credits (HTTP 400 credit
balance too low) was wrongly reported as a subscription weekly limit.

Centralize the Anthropic limit vocabulary in teatree.llm.anthropic_limits
(keyed on the bundled claude CLI's own error strings and the SDK's
five_hour/seven_day windows) and emit a per-cause message + remediation:

- API_CREDIT           -> API credits exhausted; add credits at console.anthropic.com
- SUBSCRIPTION_SESSION -> the ~5h rolling limit; resets same day
- SUBSCRIPTION_WEEKLY  -> the 7-day window; resets weekly
- RATE_LIMIT           -> transient API rate limit; retry shortly

A credit-empty key is never labeled a subscription quota.

Also detect a $0-balance metered key distinctly in the eval api_runner:
a credit-empty mid-run now raises CreditExhaustedError with the console
remediation instead of redding every remaining scenario behind an opaque
error result.
